  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "docker security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for docker is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Docker is a product for you to build, ship and run any application as a lightweight container.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nMoby is an open source container framework. Prior to version 29.3.1, a security vulnerability has been detected that allows attackers to bypass authorization plugins (AuthZ). This issue has been patched in version 29.3.1.(CVE-2026-34040)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for docker is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-24.03-LTS.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "docker",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
